require-await.description:
Description

This rule warns async functions which have noawaitexpression.

Examples ofincorrectcode for this rule:

/*eslint require-await: "error"*/

async function foo() {
    doSomething();
}

bar(async () => {
    doSomething();
});

Examples ofcorrectcode for this rule:

/*eslint require-await: "error"*/

async function foo() {
    await doSomething();
}

bar(async () => {
    await doSomething();
});

function baz() {
    doSomething();
}

bar(() => {
    doSomething();
});

async function resourceManagement() {
    await using resource = getAsyncResource();
    resource.use();
}

// Allow empty functions.
async function noop() {}
